@{
    ViewBag.Title = "About";
}
<main aria-labelledby="title">
    <h4>Tech Stack</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>ASP.NET MVC (.NET Framework 4.8)</li>
        <li>Entity Framework Database First</li>
        <li>SQL Server</li>
        <li>Bootstrap 5</li>
        <li>Chart.js</li>
        <li>Razor Views</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Database Tables & Relationships</h4>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Departments</strong> (1 -&gt; M) Students, Courses</li>
        <li><strong>Semesters</strong> (1 -&gt; M) Enrollments</li>
        <li><strong>Students</strong> (M -&gt; 1) Departments; (1 -&gt; M) Enrollments</li>
        <li><strong>Courses</strong> (M -&gt; 1) Departments; (1 -&gt; M) Enrollments</li>
        <li><strong>Enrollments</strong> (M -&gt; 1) Students, Courses, Semesters</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Purpose & Working</h4>
    <p>
        Perform CRUD operations on each entity.
        View statistics via a dashboard that visualizes:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Number of students per department (bar chart)</li>
        <li>Number of enrollments per course (pie chart)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The MVC pattern separates concerns between Models, Views, and Controllers for maintainable code.</p>
</main>